  "prompt": "How good is Vienna's medical university?",
  "response": "Vienna's Medical University, officially known as the Medical University of Vienna (MedUni Vienna), is one of the most prestigious medical schools in Europe. Here are some points to give you a sense of its reputation and standing:\n\n1. **History and Prestige**: Founded in 1365, MedUni Vienna has a long and distinguished history. It is one of the oldest medical schools in the world and has been home to numerous renowned physicians and researchers throughout its history.\n\n2. **Rankings**: The university is consistently ranked among the top medical schools globally. In various international rankings, it is recognized for its high-quality education and research output.\n\n3. **Research Excellence**: MedUni Vienna is known for its strong emphasis on research, with numerous publications in high-impact journals. It is involved in cutting-edge research in areas such as cancer, neurodegenerative diseases, and personalized medicine.\n\n4. **Facilities and Resources**: The university has state-of-the-art facilities, including the Vienna General Hospital (AKH), one of the largest hospitals in Europe, which serves as a teaching hospital. This provides students with access to a broad array of clinical experiences.\n\n5. **International Collaboration**: The university has numerous international partnerships and collaborations, enhancing its research capacities and offering students and faculty opportunities for exchange and collaboration.\n\n6. **Education Quality**: The curriculum at MedUni Vienna is noted for its rigorous and comprehensive approach, preparing students thoroughly for careers in medicine. It combines traditional medical education with innovative teaching methods.\n\n7. **Language**: The primary language of instruction is German, so proficiency in the language is necessary for enrolment, although there are some programs and courses available in English, particularly at the postgraduate level.\n\nOverall, MedUni Vienna is highly regarded and considered one of the leading institutions in the field of medical education and research in Europe and worldwide.",
